# aidaniciete.com

Personal portfolio website built as part of CIS 041 coursework at San Jose City College.  
Live site: [aidaniciete.com](https://aidaniciete.com)

-----

## Overview

This project is a personal portfolio site hosted on GitHub Pages with a custom domain configured through Porkbun. It showcases my professional background, projects, and technical skills developed through coursework and hands-on work experience.

-----

## Features

- **Portfolio & Case Studies** — Project writeups and documentation of professional work
- **Google Sheets API Integration** — Live data pulled from Google Sheets via JavaScript
- **AIS Audit Sandbox** — Interactive accounting information systems demo
- **Responsive Design** — Mobile-friendly layout across all pages

-----

## Tech Stack

|Layer           |Technology             |
|----------------|-----------------------|
|Hosting         |GitHub Pages           |
|Domain          |Porkbun (custom domain)|
|Frontend        |HTML, CSS, JavaScript  |
|Data Integration|Google Sheets API      |

-----

## Project Structure

```
aidaniciete.com/
├── index.html          # Homepage
├── /assets             # Images, icons, stylesheets
├── /projects           # Case study and project pages
├── lemonade.html       # Accounting learning game
├── vgc-guide.html      # VGC field guide
└── ...
```

-----

## Setup & Deployment

This site deploys automatically via GitHub Pages on every push to the `main` branch.

To run locally, clone the repo and open `index.html` in a browser — no build step required.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/[your-username]/[your-repo].git
cd [your-repo]
open index.html
```

-----

## Course Context

**Course:** CIS 041 — Computer Applications and Information Systems  
**Institution:** San Jose City College  


This repo demonstrates practical application of web publishing, file management, and JavaScript-based integrations covered in the course.

